==English==

===Etymology===
From {{prefix|be|wilder|lang=en}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/bɪˈwɪldə(ɹ)/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/bɪˈwɪldəɹ/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪldə(ɹ)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[confuse]], [[puzzle]] or [[befuddle]] someone, especially with many different things.
#: {{ux|en|All the different possible options may '''bewilder''' us.}}
#* {{RQ:Vance Nobody|II}}
#*: She wakened in sharp panic, '''bewildered''' by the grotesquerie of some half-remembered dream in contrast with the harshness of inclement fact, drowsily realising that since she had fallen asleep it had come on to rain smartly out of a shrouded sky.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[disorientate]] someone.
#: {{ux|en|Don't push me into that maze and '''bewilder''' me.}}

